{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17623276","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17623276"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:09:45+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:09:45+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16855"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16855","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16855"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.02,0.27,0.23,0.48]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9545"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75272"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9545","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9545"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16855"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60780"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1003"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5090"},{"type":"tags","id":"8091"},{"type":"tags","id":"9833"},{"type":"tags","id":"9835"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22550"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22552"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75272","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75272"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe coagulation cascade is a complex series of enzymatic reactions that leads to blood clot formation.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the initial step of the coagulation cascade in response to a blood vessel injury?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Factor VIII activates factor X","Thrombin cleaves fibrinogen","Factor XII activates factor XI","Platelets bind to collagen","Tissue factor binds to factor VII"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe coagulation cascade is initiated when tissue factor is exposed following vessel injury. Once exposed, \u003Cstrong\u003Etissue factor binds and activates factor VII\u003C/strong\u003E (referred to as VIIa) beginning the\u003Cstrong\u003E extrinsic pathway of coagulation.\u003C/strong\u003E The tissue factor-factor VIIa complex then activates factor X, leading to the common pathway.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFactor XII activates factor XI\u003C/strong\u003E - This is part of the intrinsic pathway, which is not the primary initiator of coagulation in vivo\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThrombin cleaves fibrinogen\u003C/strong\u003E - This occurs at the end of the common pathway, not the beginning of the cascade\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFactor VIII activates factor X\u003C/strong\u003E - Factor VIII acts as a cofactor for factor IXa to activate factor X, a step in the intrinsic pathway\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPlatelets bind to collagen\u003C/strong\u003E - While this is part of primary haemostasis, it is not part of the coagulation cascade\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The coagulation cascade is initiated in vivo by tissue factor exposure following vessel injury","The extrinsic pathway begins with factor VII binding to exposed tissue factor","The extrinsic pathway is the primary initiator of clot formation in vivo"],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019","Smith SA, Travers RJ, Morrissey JH. How it all starts: Initiation of the clotting cascade. Crit Rev Biochem Mol Biol. 2015;50(4):326-336. doi:10.3109/10409238.2015.1050550"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60780"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16855"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60780","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60780"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-29T15:56:19+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-29T15:57:15+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9545"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75272"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"1003","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1003"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Clotting factors","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":nu